            <div class="about-descriptions">
              <p class="about-description">Erwin has over 40 years of experience working as a professional carpenter. Beginning as a 15-year old apprentice to Ralph Younker in Charlottetown, he worked for several different contractors around the Island before moving to Calgary in 1981. While in Calgary he worked exlusively with siding with his brother-in-law Clyde MacEachern.</p>
              <p class="about-description">In 1988 Erwin returned to PEI and continued to work with different contractors before starting Master Exteriors in 2000.</p>
              <p class="about-description">Erwin now lives in Winsloe with his partner Anita, their dog Tillie, their mule Bella, and their two horses. </p>
